Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph search

search

Purpose:
  Find Wiki Graph objects from query text.

Use when:
  - You have words, names, phrases, or concepts and need candidate object URIs.

Usage:
  wikigraph <archive-uri> search <query> [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri> search <query> [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/<entity|triple|source|summary|chunk> search <query> [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/<entity|triple|source|summary|chunk> search <query> [--all] [--limit <n>] [--context <n>] [--evidence [n]] [--backlinks] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl] [--help|-h]

Returns:
  - In text output, a ranked list of full `wkg://...` URIs.
  - With a machine-readable format, search result items.

Notes:
  - Search requires a current FTS index. If the index is missing or outdated, run `<archive-uri>/index build`.
  - Search results are leads, not source evidence.
  - Search the archive URI for broad discovery.
  - Search a lens URI such as `<archive-uri>/source`, `<archive-uri>/summary`, `<archive-uri>/chunk`, `<archive-uri>/entity`, or `<archive-uri>/triple` to choose one object kind.
  - Lens position controls scope: `<archive-uri>/entity` searches archive-wide entities, while `<chapter-uri>/entity` searches entities scoped to one chapter.
  - Use `_` as an any-value placeholder in triple pattern lenses such as `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1/_/Q2`.
  - Trailing triple placeholders may be omitted: `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1` means `<archive-uri>/triple/Q1/_/_`.
  - Put the lens after a chapter URI, such as `<chapter-uri>/entity`, to keep retrieval local to one chapter.
  - Add `--evidence` or `--evidence <n>` to include source evidence previews on entity and triple results.
  - Source and summary search hits, plus evidence previews, include 2 nearby sentences before and after by default. Use `--context 0` for exact matched or cited ranges.
  - Add `--backlinks` to include reverse references on top-level source results; nested evidence sources are not expanded.
  - Read `wikigraph help retrieval` before choosing `--limit`, `--all`, `--json`, or `--jsonl`.
  - Use `wikigraph next <cursor>` for any returned `nextCursor`.
  - Use a located chapter URI to keep retrieval local.
  - Read `wikigraph help uri` before constructing Wiki Graph URIs; bare filesystem paths are not valid object command inputs.

Next steps:
  - Use `get` to inspect a readable returned URI.
  - Use `evidence` when source-backed verification is needed.
  - Use `pack` after selecting a useful readable URI.

Examples:
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg search "恩典 婴儿洗礼"
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg/source search "infant baptism"
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg/entity search "infant baptism"
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg/chapter/3/source search "infant baptism"
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg/chapter/3/entity search "infant baptism"
  wikigraph wkg:///books/book.wikg/triple/_/_/Q178561 search "battle"
